dc_description_s: Venice Shopping Facilities is a point theme representing shopping destinations identified as grocery stores (only chains and other locally known large grocery stores), or a complex of businesses, such as retail stores and restaurants, grouped together and sharing common services such as parking or utilities in Venice, Italy. A shopping facility is represented by multiple point objects when it has names in multiple languages. A full description of Facility Type codes and Chain ID codes can be obtained from the Metadata-Reference Classes layer.
